  <Content headline="Getting there and practical info" id="getting_there" bg="darker">
    <p>Whether you arrive by wing, rail, or road ‚Äî here‚Äôs how to find your way to the Forest.</p>
    <div id="travel_info">
      <div>
        <h4>By Plane</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Take a plane to <strong>Brussels Airport</strong> (Zaventem)</li>
          <li>Walk to the airport <strong>train station</strong></li>
          <li>Take the train from the airport to <strong>Brussels Central Station</strong></li>
          <li>Trains run every 15 minutes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>By Train</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Take the train to <strong>Brussels Central Station</strong></li>
          <li>
            All travel instructions and timetables are available on the <a href="https://www.belgiantrain.be/en"
              >Belgian Train website</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>By Foot</h4>
        <p>From <strong>Brussels Central Station</strong>, the hotel is a short walk away</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h4>By Car</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>The hotel is located within <strong>Brussels' LEZ (Low Emission Zone)</strong></li>
          <li>Older, diesel, or highly polluting cars cannot enter the city</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Registration is mandatory</strong> for all vehicles registered outside Belgium (except The Netherlands)
          </li>
          <li>Failing to register can result in a ‚Ç¨350 fine</li>
          <li>More info at <a href="https://lez.brussels/mytax/en/">LEZ info site</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
